message.content: cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.SC, cs.ET - The paper deals with algorithms for floor-planning in VLSI chip design, which involves computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also presents lower bounds on the worst-case area, which falls under the scope of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithm, which could be categorized under cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) or cs.ET (Emerging Technologies).
